Plot 1: Dont Driving Around at 4:30PM In this plot, we use wordcloud to display the times when there were accidents happened at that time frequently. Since we have more than 140000 records in this table, so we select the accidents happened in Q1 (Date between 01/01/2014 and 31/03/2014) and we only display the time when there is at least 5 accidents happened (min.freq = 5). In the plot, the larger the time is, the more accidents had happened at that time. We see the biggest character is 16:30. Therefore, you might dont want to drive at 4:30 pm in London, ^___^. (We simply want to practice wordclod in this plot, try something new!)

Plot 2: Accidents number ~ Weather Conditions, Road Surface Conditions and Speed limit In this plot, we try to look at the influences of different conditions, including weather, road surface and speed limit. Plot 3: Geographical Distribution of Accidents As we mentioned before, there are too many records in the table so we select 1% of the accidents based on Accident Index. This plot is pretty straight forward, the more concentrated the dot is, the more accidents happened in that area.
